Package dk.via.sep.shared.networking.eventServerRemote

Interface EventClientCallback

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.rmi.Remote
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    EventClientImpl
    public interface EventClientCallback
extends java.rmi.Remote
    The client callback interface that the server needs to call methods on the client. If you need to call methods on the client from the server, add them below. All methods implemented here need to throw a Remote Exception as per RMI's specification.

    • Method Summary

      Modifier and Type Method Description
      void eventCreated​(Event event)
      Method used to notify a client of a newly added event.
      void eventEdited​(Event event)
      Method used to notify a client of a newly edited event.
      void eventRemoved​(Event event)
      Method used to notify a client of a removed event.
      void retrieveEventList​(java.util.ArrayList<Event> events)
      Method used to send the list of events back to the client.
